      OUR LEADERSHIP
    </span>

    <h2>
      Meet Our Leadership Team
    </h2>

    <p>
      Compassion Bridge Initiative Uganda is guided by a dedicated team of
      passionate leaders committed to restoring dignity and building brighter
      futures.
    </p>

  </div>

  <div class="leaders-grid">

    <div class="leader-card">

      <img src="/director.png" alt="Peter Waiswa">

      <h3>Peter Waiswa</h3>

      <h4>Director</h4>

      <p>
        Peter Waiswa is an Accountant by profession. After graduating from
        university, he worked with one of Uganda's local banks before leaving
        to co-found Such As I Have Foundation and later Compassion Bridge
        Initiative Uganda.
      </p>

      <p>
        He is also the National Coordinator of the Global Compassion Coalition
        Connectors Programme in Uganda, a scholar of the Amnesty International
        Human Rights Academy and a passionate environmentalist.
      </p>

    </div>


    <div class="leader-card">

      <img src="/nakato.png" alt="Nakato Faridah">

      <h3>Nakato Faridah</h3>

      <h4>Chairperson</h4>

      <p>
        Nakato Faridah is a graduate of Social Sciences with vast experience
        in women and children affairs.
      </p>

      <p>
        She currently serves as Secretary for Women Affairs on the Sub-county
        Local Government Council and is the Chairperson of Compassion Bridge
        Initiative Uganda.
      </p>

    </div>


    <div class="leader-card">

      <img src="/andrew.png" alt="Andrew Sembela">

      <h3>Andrew Sembela</h3>

      <h4>Vice Chairperson</h4>

      <p>
        Andrew is a graduate of Business Administration and works with Airtel
        Uganda as a Business Representative.
      </p>

      <p>
        He has served on several NGO advisory boards and currently serves as
        Vice Chairperson of Compassion Bridge Initiative Uganda.
      </p>

    </div>


    <div class="leader-card">

      <img src="/christine.png" alt="Christine Wamwanina">

      <h3>Christine Wamwanina</h3>

      <h4>Treasurer</h4>

      <p>
        Christine Wamwanina is a qualified teacher, advocate for women and
        children's rights and one of the co-founders of Compassion Bridge
        Initiative Uganda.
      </p>

      <p>
        She currently serves as Treasurer of the Board and plays a key role
        in the organisation's growth and community programmes.
      </p>

    </div>

  </div>

